Date: 0/0/1959
Source: Gun in My Hand, A
Author: SLATTER
Vol / Page: 148
Edition:
Quote: Poor country lads the Hun radio called them, poor country lads who gave the German professionals plenty of stoush. The easy-going jokers who jacked things up with the she'll-be-right spirit. ... Ingenuity the war correspondents called it. Like the bloke who looted a three-toned horn from an Ite garage and fitted it to his stores truck. And sounded it majestically through the narrow streets of the Castelraimondo. Toodle-ay-eh. A wild colonial boy. The irrepressible she'll-be-right New Zealander. They made good.
